{"TopicId":191552,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"mirror pieces","CreatedByName":"jaunco325","CreatedById":198491,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-11T17:26:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"jaunco325","CreatedById":198491,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-11T17:26:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that allows me to mirror some pieces? example: that allows to make that in the airplane cabins, the kerbal leaves by the right side instead of the left.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shadowmage","CreatedById":138730,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-11T23:15:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739332\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581441963\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198491\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jaunco325\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, jaunco325 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that allows me to mirror some pieces? example: that allows to make that in the airplane cabins, the kerbal leaves by the right side instead of the left.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might be able to effect this with a simple \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch, by setting the scale on the X axis of the model to a negative value (e.g. scale = -1,1,1).\u00A0 That is traditionally how things are \u0027mirrored\u0027 in 3d modeling, but I cannot guarantee that KSP will handle it all properly, especially if the part in question involves animations or other complicated modules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jaunco325","CreatedById":198491,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-12T15:59:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would not erase the original configuration of the piece?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-12T16:18:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739789\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581523193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198491\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jaunco325\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, jaunco325 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would not erase the original configuration of the piece?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuse the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E Patch to copy the part\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002BPART instead of \u003Cspan\u003E@PART\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jaunco325","CreatedById":198491,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-13T05:24:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not understand\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-13T05:50:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739531\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581462950\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138730\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shadowmage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2020 at 11:15 PM, Shadowmage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might be able to effect this with a simple \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E patch, by setting the scale on the X axis of the model to a negative value (e.g. scale = -1,1,1).\u00A0 That is traditionally how things are \u0027mirrored\u0027 in 3d modeling, but I cannot guarantee that KSP will handle it all properly, especially if the part in question involves animations or other complicated modules.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739789\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581523193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198491\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jaunco325\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/12/2020 at 3:59 PM, jaunco325 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would not erase the original configuration of the piece?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739800\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581524332\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190933\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zer0Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/12/2020 at 4:18 PM, zer0Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nuse the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Module Manager (mod)\u0022\u003EMM\u003C/abbr\u003E Patch to copy the part\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002BPART instead of \u003Cspan\u003E@PART\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso you could create a module manager patch to copy the part and possibly mirror it - that way you would have two parts - one left, one right.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do not know if this would work, never tried.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso the beginnings of the patch would start something like this:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-c prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E\u002B\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EPART\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Epart name here\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E]:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EFOR\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EzzzzMe\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E@name\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E^=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E$\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E:-\u003C/spa